<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880721-0056 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: National Broadcasting Co. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GE </CO><TEXT>   The NBC television network chose advertising agency D'Arcy Masius Benton andamp; Bowles Inc. to create print advertising for its miniseries, movies and entertainment specials.    The New York agency's Los Angeles office will handle the account, which is expected to bill about $30 million annually. D'Arcy will plan media buying with NBC's in-house advertising staff and will handle placement of all print, outdoor and radio advertisements.    The National Broadcasting Co. division's account previously was handled by ACandamp;R/DHB andamp; Bess, a Saatchi andamp; Saatchi PLC unit. New York-based NBC-TV is a subsidiary of General Electric Co. </TEXT></DOC>